---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="My Story · Anuyu"
  description="The real story behind the practice: trauma, transformation, and the work of coming home to yourself."
>

  <!-- ===== story page header ===== -->
  <header class="journal-head">
    <div class="eyebrow">My Story</div>
    <h1>If you're here, you're probably <span class="ital">tired of surviving.</span></h1>
    <p class="blurb">
      Tired of repeating the same patterns. Tired of carrying pain you
      don't fully understand. Tired of knowing there must be more to
      life than just getting through the day.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- ===== story body ===== -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 48px;">
    <div class="story">

      <aside class="story-portrait">
        <img class="portrait" src="/assets/portrait-anuyu.png" alt="Portrait of Anu" />
        <div class="portrait-caption">
          <span class="orn" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          Anu, founder of the practice
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="story-body">

        <div class="post-epigraph" style="margin: 0 0 48px;">
          <blockquote>
            You are not broken. You are in the middle of becoming.
          </blockquote>
        </div>

        <p class="story-lede" style="max-width: 56ch;">
          My name is Anu, and I am here to accompany you through the most
          important inquiry of your life: the one that begins when you
          finally stop running and turn toward yourself.
        </p>
        <p class="story-lede" style="max-width: 56ch; margin-top: -28px;">
          I am a former physician, now a Mind-Body Practitioner and Life
          Coach. But more than anything, I am someone who has made this
          journey herself. The long way. With honesty, humility, and lived
          experience.
        </p>

        <div class="story-chapter" id="beginning">
          <div class="chapter-num">i · The beginning</div>
          <h3>A life shaped by trauma, transformed by healing.</h3>
          <p>
            I often say, <em>"I was never really a child."</em> My early
            years were marked by silence and experiences that forced me
            to grow up too soon. Those experiences left patterns that
            kept repeating through my adult life.
          </p>
          <p>
            Later came profound losses: the passing of my father, the
            loss of my mother, leaving my home country, heartbreaks, and
            a life-altering surgery that changed my relationship with my
            body forever. For many years, I lived in survival mode.
            High-functioning on the outside. Disconnected, grieving, and
            searching on the inside.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="story-chapter" id="turning">
          <div class="chapter-num">ii · The turning</div>
          <h3>The moment I stopped running, and turned toward the pain.</h3>
          <p>
            There were moments when I truly believed: <em>"I can't be
            the only one living like this, but I don't know how to
            change."</em> That question became the beginning of my
            transformation.
          </p>
          <p>
            Instead of running from my pain, I turned towards it.
            Instead of numbing, I listened. And slowly, through healing,
            study, and deep inner work, I began to understand something
            powerful:
          </p>
          <blockquote>
            Pain is not the end of the story. It is often the doorway
            to your true self.
          </blockquote>
        </div>

        <div class="story-chapter" id="path">
          <div class="chapter-num">iii · From medicine to mind-body</div>
          <h3>Integrating science with spirituality.</h3>
          <p>
            My professional path began in science. I studied medicine
            and started practising in 2014. From 2011 onward, I worked
            closely with cancer patients. Sitting with people at the
            edge of life taught me something no textbook ever could:
            that the human spirit is far stronger, wiser, and more
            resilient than we realize.
          </p>
          <p>
            My father used to say, <em>"Death is nothing but the
            beginning of a new journey."</em> Over time, I learned that
            transformation doesn't only happen through physical death.
            It happens every time we let go of an old identity, an old
            wound, an old story.
          </p>
          <p>
            As my own healing deepened, I felt called to integrate
            science with spirituality. That path led me to become a
            Mind-Body Practitioner and Holistic Life Coach, where I
            developed an approach that works on every level:
          </p>
          <ul class="story-list defined">
            <li><span class="term">the conscious mind</span><span class="brk" aria-hidden="true"></span><span class="def">what you think</span></li>
            <li><span class="term">the subconscious</span><span class="def">what you believe without knowing it</span></li>
            <li><span class="term">the nervous system</span><span class="def">what your body is still holding</span></li>
            <li><span class="term">the emotional body</span><span class="def">what you feel but rarely name</span></li>
            <li><span class="term">and something deeper still</span><span class="def">what you sense but can't always articulate</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="story-chapter" id="work">
          <div class="chapter-num">iv · Why I do this work</div>
          <h3>To help people come home to themselves.</h3>
          <p>
            Today, my purpose is simple, and deeply personal: to help
            people come home to themselves. I work with people who are:
          </p>
          <ul class="story-list accented">
            <li>stuck in repeating emotional patterns</li>
            <li>navigating grief, heartbreak, or major transitions</li>
            <li>disconnected from their body or identity</li>
            <li>struggling with self-worth and self-trust</li>
            <li>searching for purpose, clarity, and peace</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Through coaching, we don't just talk about your problems.
            We gently uncover where they began. We release what no
            longer serves you. And we rewire the beliefs and patterns
            that have been quietly shaping your life.
          </p>
          <p>
            My clients don't come to <em>fix</em> themselves. They
            come to remember who they truly are, beneath the
            conditioning, the trauma, and the fear.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="post-signature" style="margin-top: 56px;">
          <img src="/assets/signature.png" alt="Love, Anu signed" />
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== closing CTA ===== -->
  <section class="section" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); padding: 64px 0 32px;">
    <div class="post-bottom" style="margin: 0 auto; max-width: none;">

      <div class="bottom-card">
        <div class="bottom-eyebrow">Begin</div>
        <h3>Ready to come <span class="ital">home to yourself?</span></h3>
        <p>Begin with a quiet check-in. Ten short questions to show me where you are right now. I'll write back personally within a few days.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/check-in">
          Get Your Free Personalized Assessment
          <span class="btn-arrow" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </a>
        <p style="margin-top: 18px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink-faint);">
          Or, if you'd rather just write,
          <a href="mailto:anuyu.coach@gmail.com" style="color: var(--ink); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);">say hello at anuyu.coach@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bottom-card">
        <div class="bottom-eyebrow">See the work</div>
        <h3>The <span class="ital">three offerings</span> I currently hold.</h3>
        <p>The Untangle, the 28-day "A New You" programme, and a free hello. Choose the offering that meets your season.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/offerings">Explore offerings</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
